<ol><li>A narrow&nbsp;<b>beam of electrons</b>&nbsp;in a <b>vacuum tube</b>&nbsp;is directed at a thin&nbsp;<b>metal foil</b>.</li><li>The electrons in the beam&nbsp;<b>passes through the metal foil</b>&nbsp;and are&nbsp;<u>diffracted in certain directions only</u>. Forming a pattern of&nbsp;<b>concentric rings</b>&nbsp;on a fluorescent screen at the end of the tube.</li></ol>